</CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubrairwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brairwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/8/02 8:49:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=251.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Money and melee</span><hr size=1> True tradeskills can make alot of money, however (This is from an amorsmith of about 550ish)  that it can be boring and does take time.  I know at 25 that damp mites make far better money than crafting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udragoon412.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dragoon412</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/8/02 9:00:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=251.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Money and melee</span><hr size=1> Hrm...<br>
<br>
I wasn't aware you could make -that- much money doing consignments; I started powerskilling my healer in armorcrafting -- I'm around 260 with all my secondary skills within 5 points  and my tailoring as high as it can get right now, and it's run me about 7 gold. I finally gave up because I couldn't stand the tedium anymore, and I've heard it only gets worse.<br>
<br>
So for the time being, my trouble's with my paladin (piercing defensive build... I'm going for the uber tank thing). Anyone have any suggestions for hunting in Albion? I just scrapped my other 2-handed pally... I dinged and was suddenly stuck with a blue weapon, 2 pieces of blue armor, the rest green, and no cash to upgrade, even though all I'd done for 2 levels straight was solo (green) dragon ants. <p>--For every winner, there are dozens of losers. Odds are you're one of 'em. 
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugallatin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gallatin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/8/02 9:11:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=251.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://astro.temple.edu/~fmoffat/img/kitty6.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Money and melee</span><hr size=1> Drag, consignment money gets better the higher you go, and there are sweet spots in the curve. As a fletcher, there are some spots where I don't want to gain any fletching points, I just want to keep making the big commission bows :-)<br>
<br>
I'm at 521 currently. <p><b>Gallatin</b><p>
<font size=1><a><a href=http://www.fridgemagnet.org.uk/kitchen.html>"Start cleaning up after your disgusting messy self, you utter, utter filthy bastard."</a></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaliciaswiftfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salicia Swiftfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>DAOC Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/8/02 9:11:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=251.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Money and melee</span><hr size=1> Well, I've played all 3 realms pretty evenly now, and I can honestly say that getting money for your low level equipment in Albion has to be the hardest, followed by midgard. (I never have had money problems in Hibernia - a lot of mobs are grouped and drop treasure chests at low levels and I think that has a lot to do with it)  One thing that will make you feel better though.  Around level 15 or so, your money situation will start to reverse as the monsters start to drop more money and better items.  Also, if you fight in the low level dungeons, you'll be able to equip yourself in low level monster drop items.  There are also quite a few armor/weapon quests you can do to help outfit yourself. (I'd check Kazams for that info)<br>
<br>
Once you hit your mid to high 30's, you won't have money problems at all anymore.  I know several people in their mid to high 40's with 5 to 10 plat that they carry around with them. (1000 gold = 1 plat mind you) <p><table><tr><td height=1 width=1><img src=http://divineguildpics.homestead.com/files/galadriel.gif border=0><td valign="bottom"><b><font size=4 color=0066FF>Salicia Swiftfoot</b><br></font><font size=2 color=red><i>Theurgist to the Stars</i></font><br><font size=2 color=0066FF><b>Galahad Server<br>DAoC Moderator for <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove>The Druids Grove</a></b></td>
</tr>
</table><a href=http://meridian59.neardeathstudios.com/ target="_blank">
<font size=1 color=red>Meridian 59 lives!</a> - Salicia of 102</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unyssarainwhisper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyssa Rainwhisper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/bluepawbullet.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/8/02 10:31:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=251.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/zidane.gif WIDTH=64 HEIGHT=64></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Money and melee</span><hr size=1> To be honest, while doing commissions in tradeskills are awesome for money, you don't begin making the big bucks till post 500 skill.  I powerskilled to 300 and started doing commissions then and was making just enough for me to buy materials and continue advancing.  Mythic designed tradeskills to net you a 7-12% profit with each item, depending on the quality lvl.  (It used to be up to 17% but was nerfed about a month or 2 ago so people with 1st lvl tradeskill mules didn't have more money than say a 40th lvl who just hunts.)  I started doing tradeskills after the commission nerf starting out with about 30g.  When commissions stopped for me at 650 skill, I had a bit over 400g to my name, and over 200g of that came from my last 100-150 skills.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind that I'm an armor crafter.  Different professions net different results.  I have heard that fletching is one of the least profitable skills.<br>
<br>
Sure tradeskills gets boring in the long run, but it's not much worse than sitting in one spot for hours and hours farming greens for cash.  Powerskilling is by far the most boring part of tradeskills.  Commissions are a bit better because you run around the city getting to know where all the NPCs are and what they sell or do.  Grab a book and craft away.  I've peeled through several great books while getting my armor crafting to 650. <p><CENTER>
